problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in philosophy would. In the diagram shown here (which is not drawn to scale), suppose that $\triangle ABC \sim \triangle PAQ$ and $\triangle ABQ \sim \triangle QCP$.  If $m\angle BAC = 70^\circ$, then compute $m\angle PQC$. [asy]
size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
pair B = (0,0), C = (6,0), A = (2,4), Q = (1,0), P = (A + C)/2;
draw(A--B--C--A--Q--P);
label("$B$",B,S); label("$A$",A,N); label("$C$",C,S); label("$P$",P,E); label("$Q$",Q,S);
[/asy]

